<h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
<p>Gratitude is a state of the highest vibration. Gratitude Tokens play with the cryptocurrency mechanics, by creating a physical token incentivising expressing gratitude within a community in a playful way.</p>

<h2 id="prep">Prep</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Prepare tokens by cutting a thick branch into small coins. Make sure there‚Äôs at least one per person, plus a few additional tokens.</li>
  <li>Prepare a few markers and a pen.</li>
  <li>Grab a notebook (or a few pieces of paper) and create a Gratitude Token Ledger. Draw the Gratitude Token symbol on the cover page, then write tokenomics instructions on the first available page. You can then ‚Äúmint‚Äù the first token and record the first entry in the ledger (see below).</li>
  <li>Optional but fun to have: a piece of paper stating: HODL ‚â†¬†GWYC</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="/assets/hodl-gwyc.jpg" alt="HODL ‚â†¬†GWYC" /></p>

<p><img src="/assets/gratitude-token-mining-station.jpg" alt="Gratitude Token Minting Station" /></p>

<h2 id="gratitude-token-ledger">Gratitude Token Ledger</h2>
<p><img src="/assets/gratitude-token-ledger-cover.jpg" alt="Gratitude Token Ledger Cover" /></p>

<p>Below are the instructions (v1) to include in the Ledger. Feel free to modify them to fit your context. You‚Äôll find a few ideas at the end.</p>

<h3 id="tokenomics">Tokenomics</h3>
<ol>
  <li>A Gratitude Token is a physical object serving as a catalyst to express gratitude.</li>
  <li>Give your Gratitude Token(s) to people you feel grateful for.</li>
  <li>Do not HODL your tokens! Instead Give Whenever You Can ‚Äì GWYC (pronounce: QUICK)</li>
  <li>If you realise that you are HODLing Gratitude Token(s), take a moment to be grateful for all the gifts in your life and give your token(s) away to someone that deserves it.</li>
  <li>If you suspect someone is HODLing Gratitude Tokens, give them a Gratitude Token to model giving behaviour.</li>
  <li>Whenever you run out of tokens, you can mint new Gratitude Tokens at any time at your local minting station. To mint, prepare a wooden piece, draw the Gratitude Token Symbol, and add a personal mark. Next, state your Proof of Work by completing an entry in the Gratitude Token Ledger by drawing <em>your personal mark</em> and answer in writing <em>why are you minting this token.</em></li>
</ol>

<p><img src="/assets/gratitude-token-tokenomics.jpg" alt="Gratitude Token Tokenomics" /></p>

